body:
So the client is bad, we know this, Rito is implementing a new one because of such. Why has there been so many more crashes for NO apparent reason as of late? More importantly, WHY DURING CHAMP SELECT. I have lost so much LP{{item:3070}} {{item:3070}} {{item:3070}}  because of 'dodging', when the client has crashed. This happens no matter what state my overly-competant computer is doing.

I know we are getting a new client, but PLEASE INITIATE A RECONNECT BUTTON FOR CHAMP SELECT. It literally takes seconds to restart the client, but without a "reconnect" (you know, like the one in-game) you get a loss, at the hands of Riot software. Fair right?

Atleast SOME thought from Riot staff on the topic would be appreciated. I know you cant remove LP loss for dodges, people would abuse it, but atleast have a reconnect for those legitimately try-harding it. Really rewarding to support and fill (same thing right?) to have the client crash.{{champion:89}} {{champion:201}}  {{champion:40}}
